1 Download Ubuntu Server Iso From https://ubuntu.com/download/server
2 Flash The Iso Using BalenaEtcher Rufus DD Mode Ventoy Etc
3 Setup Ubuntu Server
4 If You See Choose the type of installation Its Strictly Recommended To Use Ubuntu Server (minimized) Because Ubuntu Server Minimized is highly lightweight
offering a drastically reduced package set (~50% smaller image size) that boots up to 40% faster than the standard server edition
utilizing fewer system resources and requiring fewer security updates
making it ideal for minimal footprints, though it lacks many common administrative tools. 
5 Then Wait Until Installation Finished
6 You May Stop The Services Of Snap
  sudo systemctl stop snapd
  sudo systemctl disable snapd

7 Purge Snapd (Recommended For Older Hardware Or Any Slow Hardware)
  sudo apt purge snapd

8 7 Clean Up Leftover Directories
  rm -rf ~/snap
  sudo rm -rf /var/snap /var/lib/snapd /var/cache/snapd

9 Reboot
  sudo reboot

10 System Updates: Ubuntu may reinstall Snapd during major upgrades. To prevent this, you can block Snapd from being reinstalled:
  sudo apt-mark hold snapd

11 Install IceWM And Wallpapers
  sudo apt update
  sudo apt install icewm ubuntu-wallpapers

12 Reboot Using Sudo Reboot

13 Have Fun And Start Using Ubuntu IceWM

   
